- New concurrency systems;
- New compiler systems;
- New package systems;
- New runtime systems;
- New security systems;
- New operating-system integrations.

A new version of Spider may be incompatible with earlier versions.

Spider Technologies may maintain compatibility layers, migration tools, or legacy versions, but is not obligated to do so.

No user has a permanent right to any particular language feature, syntax, version, package, or implementation.

